news.title: Over 26,000 house registrations recorded in Navi Mumbai in Jan-Mar quarter
news.para: As per the Maharashtra Chamber of Housing Industry (MCHI-Navi Mumbai), total 26,484 house sales were recorded in the registration offices in Panvel, Vashi, and CBD-Belapur, with a majority of 2,184 registrations from the five registration offices of Panvel.

news.title: Chandigarh: Four fraud FIRs against Gupta Builders & Promoters
news.para: In their complaints, Ramesh Kumar and Manju Rani, both residents of Phase X, Mohali, alleged Satish Gupta, Raman Gupta, Pardeep Gupta and others duped them of Rs 36.31 lakh on the pretext of selling plots at New Chandigarh.

news.title: Haryana to probe land deeds since 2010
news.para: Additional chief secretary (Revenue and Power) PK Das has asked the deputy commissioners to start the probe and take details from the tehsils under their districts. The communication is learned to have been made last week.

news.title: Mumbai: SRA, Mhada notice to builders of projects stuck for over five years
news.para: hile SRA has directed appointment of new developers for 517 slum rehabilitation schemes caught up prior to 2014, Mhada has issued notices to 37 developers.

news.title: Use recycled water for construction in DLF colonies: Gurugram civic body to builder
news.para: Potable water, according to the civic body, is being used for construction activities going on in DLF colonies and other areas in the city. An MCG official said underground water is being extracted for construction work illegally.

news.title: Soon, stringent regulations on sale, purchase of land in Uttarakhand likely
news.para: A committee constituted last year to recommend amendments to the land laws is likely to submit its recommendations to the state government in about 10 days.

news.title: Higher mortgage rates set stage for lower home sales in USA
news.para: A run-up in rates in recent weeks is threatening to undo that dynamic, setting the stage for a slowdown in home sales this year as the increased borrowing costs reduce would-be buyers' purchasing power.

news.title: Canadian regulator says housing downturn among biggest financial system risks
news.para: The "unprecedented run-up" in home prices has led to increasingly leveraged borrowers, which in turn increases financial institutions' exposure to a market correction, the Office of the Superintendent of Financial Institutions (OSFI) said in its first annual risk outlook report for the year ending March 31, 2023.

news.title: Bank of Baroda slashes home loan interest rate to 6.5% for limited period
news.para: "We have seen a significant pick-up in home sales over the last many months and we are delighted to extend the good times for home buyers with the introduction of a special, limited period interest rate offer of 6.50 per cent along with nil processing charges," its general manager (mortgages and other retail assets) H T Solanki said in a release.

news.title: Delhi: Slums in reserve forest face axe, residents ask where can we go
news.para: In compliance with an NGT order, the notice, sent in March this year, identified Sapera, Gulabo, Nala, Israil and Shankar camps and Rangpuri and Rajokari forest areas for eviction and asked encroachers to leave within 14 days.

news.title: ICRA revises outlook for residential real estate to stable for FY23
news.para: The revision in the outlook has been "supported by multi-year high sales which in turn is driven by increasing preference for home ownership, improved affordability, all-time-low home loan interest rate, among other factors", ICRA said in a statement.

news.title: LG admin issues order for 50% remission in stamp duty for first-time buyers in J&K
news.para: On February 25, the Administrative Council (AC), which had met under the chairmanship of Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha, had approved the remission in stamp duty for first-time property buyers.

news.title: Macrotech Developers sells office space worth 188 crore to National Realty
news.para: The local developer has bought the office space on 6th, 10th, 11st, 12th and 14th floor of one of the towers of the commercial development at Rs 11,627 per sq. ft. on carpet area basis, which is in line with the ongoing property rates in the vicinity.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to bring agenda to convert leasehold properties to freehold
news.para: The agenda was rejected during the last general house meeting along with over six other items by both the opposition parties, AAP and Congress, due to their majority in the house.

news.title: Certus Capital targets over Rs 500 crore realty investment deals in one year
news.para: The digital platform aims to strike 8-10 deals in the real estate space over the next one year. As per the structure, Certus Capital’s non-banking finance company (NBFC) holds at least 5-10% of the total loan till maturity and brings in underwriting to ensure smooth closures and certainty for the borrowers.
